<paragraph blockId="87.[189,1399,1465,1562]" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">
The description is based on the protologue and photographs of the 
<typeStatus box="[985,1039,1466,1492]" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">type</typeStatus>
; the notes therein describe the species as protandrous. This species is vegetatively similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[924,1092,1500,1526]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sikkimensis">
<emphasis box="[924,1092,1500,1526]" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">B. sikkimensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="R. Camfield" authorityYear="2018" box="[1151,1261,1500,1526]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="87" pageNumber="88" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="koelzii">
<emphasis box="[1151,1261,1500,1526]" italics="true" pageId="87" pageNumber="88">B. koelzii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in terms of having lacerate leaves; see notes under those species.
</paragraph>
